Set the editor layout. Editor layout is represented as a tree of groups in which the first group is the root group of the layout.
					The orientation of the first group is 0 (horizontal) by default unless specified otherwise. The other orientations are 1 (vertical).
					The orientation of subsequent groups is the opposite of the orientation of the group that contains it.
					Here are some examples: A layout representing 1 row and 2 columns: { orientation: 0, groups: [{}, {}] }.
					A layout representing 3 rows and 1 column: { orientation: 1, groups: [{}, {}, {}] }.
					A layout representing 3 rows and 1 column in which the second row has 2 columns: { orientation: 1, groups: [{}, { groups: [{}, {}] }, {}] }

anyOf.description: Name of the command to remove keyboard shortcut for

kind.description: The kind of the paste edit to try applying. If not provided or there are multiple edits for this kind, the editor will show a picker.

focus.description: Controls if and when the hover should take focus upon being triggered by this action.
enumDescriptions: The hover will not automatically take focus.
The hover will take focus only if it is already visible.
The hover will automatically take focus when it appears.

orientation.description: The orientation of the root group in the layout. 0 for horizontal, 1 for vertical.

query.description: The query to open the quick chat with

isPartialQuery.description: Whether the query is partial; it will wait for more user input

anyOf.description: The query to open the quick chat with

cwd.description: The directory to start the terminal at

name.description: The new name for the terminal

profileName.description: The name of the profile to create

enumDescriptions: Create the terminal in the terminal view
Create the terminal in the editor

key.description: Key or key sequence (separated by space)

then.errorMessage: Incorrect type. Expected "string". The field 'command' does not support running multiple commands. Use command 'runCommands' to pass it multiple commands to run.

when.description: Condition when the key is active.

args.description: Arguments to pass to the command to execute.

sticky.description: Stick to the end even when going to longer lines

kind.description: Kind of the code action to run.

apply.description: Controls when the returned actions are applied.
enumDescriptions: Always apply the first returned code action.
Apply the first returned code action if it is the only one.
Do not apply the returned code actions.

preferred.description: Controls if only preferred code actions should be returned.

autoReveal.description: Whether the cell should be revealed into view automatically
